==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maintainor
<hw>Main*tain"or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>mainteneor</ets>, F. <ets>mainteneur</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Crim.
Law)</fld> <def>One who, not being interested, maintains a cause
depending between others, by furnishing money, etc., to either
party.</def> <rj><au>Bouvier.</au> <au>Wharton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

